Maintainer: Barak A. Pearlmutter <bap@debian.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4.0.0)
Standards-Version: 3.6.1

Package: raidutils
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: I2O RAID controller management utilities
 The raidutil programs manage I2O-compliant RAID controllers,
 including much Adaptec hardware.  One can create/delete a RAID array,
 add/remove a hot spare drive to/from a RAID array, activate/silence
 the alarm, and get information about the status of the RAID array and
 disks.
